		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dastari wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Greetings...seems I'm having a lot of trouble these days. I've lost a screw to one of my carts. I realize that the NES screws are made for those "special bits" but I'm just going to buy a flathead equivalent like some of the early games had. Could you just let me know the type of screw that they used on the NES, both thread and length? Basically I need the same information that you can take down to the Ace Hardware store to pick up the screws. <br /><br />Thanks!</div>
<br />
<br />Aren't the NES cartridge and NES console screws reverse/inverted Torx?
<br />
<br />You can buy the bits which open them, you know.  They're available all over the place.
<br />
<br />My advice is to keep the original screws and just buy the bits needed to open the console/carts.  $15 tops, for both bits.  I think I got mine for around $12 online somewhere.

		

